\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Phelps, who returns to NBCU's coverage following his role on the Tokyo Olympics in 2021, will offer commentary and analysis on the primetime and daytime shows in Paris on NBC and Peacock, and will also join Dan Hicks and Rowdy Gaines in the booth for select swimming competition at Par\\u00eds La D\\u00e9fense Arena.Elizabeth Beiselwill serve as a correspondent/analyst andMelissa Starka reporter at the swimming venue in Paris.\", \"from\": 642, \"to\": 1059, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 642, \"end\": 648, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/William_H._Phelps_Sr.\", \"score\": 0.9999999988567652, \"rank\": 1.1432924511268672e-09, \"text\": \"Phelps\", \"types\": [\"Q901\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/William_H._Phelps_Sr.\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/William_H._Phelps_Sr.\"}, {\"begin\": 665, \"end\": 669, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBCUniversal\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"NBCU\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBCUniversal\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBCUniversal\"}, {\"begin\": 804, \"end\": 809, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.918617467072233e-17, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 813, \"end\": 816, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC_Sports\", \"score\": 0.995919019876006, \"rank\": 0.004084460172050508, \"text\": \"NBC\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC_Sports\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC_Sports\"}, {\"begin\": 821, \"end\": 828, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Peafowl\", \"score\": 0.9999999999258762, \"rank\": 7.400291655665075e-11, \"text\": \"Peacock\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Peafowl\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Peafowl\"}, {\"begin\": 849, \"end\": 858, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dan_Hicks_(singer)\", \"score\": 0.7661863309397541, \"rank\": 0.2941348117887413, \"text\": \"Dan Hicks\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q483501\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dan_Hicks_(singer)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dan_Hicks_(singer)\"}, {\"begin\": 1012, \"end\": 1018, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Starka\", \"score\": 0.9999999999895408, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Starka\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Starka\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Starka\"}, {\"begin\": 1053, \"end\": 1058, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.918617467072233e-17, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Beginning tonight at 8 p.m. ET/PT on NBC and Peacock, Phelps, who competed in five Olympic Games from 2000-16, will join Hicks and Gaines in the booth for NBC Sports' coverage of the U.S. Olympic Trials-Swimming in Indianapolis.\", \"from\": 1061, \"to\": 1289, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1098, \"end\": 1101, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC_Sports\", \"score\": 0.995919019876006, \"rank\": 0.004084460172050508, \"text\": \"NBC\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC_Sports\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC_Sports\"}, {\"begin\": 1106, \"end\": 1113, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Peafowl\", \"score\": 0.9999999999258762, \"rank\": 7.400291655665075e-11, \"text\": \"Peacock\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Peafowl\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Peafowl\"}, {\"begin\": 1115, \"end\": 1121, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/William_H._Phelps_Sr.\", \"score\": 0.9999999988567652, \"rank\": 1.1432924511268672e-09, \"text\": \"Phelps\", \"types\": [\"Q901\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/William_H._Phelps_Sr.\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/William_H._Phelps_Sr.\"}, {\"begin\": 1216, \"end\": 1226, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC_Sports\", \"score\": 0.9999999977585503, \"rank\": 1.961656898408378e-09, \"text\": \"NBC Sports\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC_Sports\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC_Sports\"}, {\"begin\": 1276, \"end\": 1288, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Indianapolis\", \"score\": 0.9999986956890419, \"rank\": 1.2321547197393787e-06, \"text\": \"Indianapolis\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Indianapolis\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Indianapolis\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"We are excited to have Michael return to our coverage across both daytime and primetime, and of course, the place where no one knows more about winning - at the pool,\\\" said Molly Solomon, Executive Producer & President, NBC Olympics Production.\", \"from\": 1291, \"to\": 1536, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1465, \"end\": 1470, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Molly_Hayes\", \"score\": 0.7901429101300466, \"rank\": 0.26554730974752283, \"text\": \"Molly\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Molly_Hayes\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Molly_Hayes\"}, {\"begin\": 1512, \"end\": 1524, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC_Olympic_broadcasts\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"NBC Olympics\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\", \"Q15416\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC_Olympic_broadcasts\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC_Olympic_broadcasts\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"With his ability to analyze and entertain, our viewers are in for another gold-medal performance.\\\"\", \"from\": 1537, \"to\": 1636, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"***  In Paris this summer, the world's greatest athletes will compete against the backdrop of one of the most beautiful cities in the world where the modern Olympic Games were conceived 130 years ago.\", \"from\": 1638, \"to\": 1838, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1646, \"end\": 1651, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.918617467072233e-17, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This will be the third time Paris has hosted the Olympics (1900 and 1924), tying London for the most as a Summer Games host.\", \"from\": 1839, \"to\": 1963, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1867, \"end\": 1872, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.918617467072233e-17, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 1920, \"end\": 1926, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\", \"score\": 0.999999650798206, \"rank\": 1.9552387279573016e-07, \"text\": \"London\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Los Angeles (1932, 1984) will tie those two cities when it hosts the first Summer Games in the U.S. in 32 years in 2028.\", \"from\": 1964, \"to\": 2084, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1964, \"end\": 1975, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\", \"score\": 0.9999999737942747, \"rank\": 2.6203671486999927e-08, \"text\": \"Los Angeles\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Paris organizers are reimagining the Games to make them more accessible to the public and to showcase their city to the world.\", \"from\": 2086, \"to\": 2216, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2090, \"end\": 2095, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.918617467072233e-17, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In a first, competitions will be held amidst iconic Parisian landmarks - beach volleyball at the Eiffel Tower, equestrian at the Palace of Versailles, and urban sports at Place de la Concorde.\", \"from\": 2217, \"to\": 2409, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2388, \"end\": 2408, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Place_de_la_Concorde\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.854955535552306e-16, \"text\": \"Place de la Concorde\", \"types\": [\"Q34442\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Place_de_la_Concorde\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Place_de_la_Concorde\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The surfing competition will take place nearly 10,000 miles from Paris in Tahiti, a part of French Polynesia.\", \"from\": 2410, \"to\": 2519, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2475, \"end\": 2480, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.918617467072233e-17, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 2484, \"end\": 2490, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tahiti\", \"score\": 0.9999005811948345, \"rank\": 9.788768883480519e-05, \"text\": \"Tahiti\", \"types\": [\"Q23442\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tahiti\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tahiti\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The NBC broadcast network and streaming service Peacock will be the company's primary platforms for its coverage of the Olympic Games Paris 2024, scheduled for July 26-Aug. 11.\", \"from\": 2521, \"to\": 2697, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2525, \"end\": 2528, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC_Sports\", \"score\": 0.995919019876006, \"rank\": 0.004084460172050508, \"text\": \"NBC\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC_Sports\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC_Sports\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Clickherefor more linear programming information andherefor more about the Olympic experience on Peacock.\", \"from\": 2698, \"to\": 2803, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2795, \"end\": 2802, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Peafowl\", \"score\": 0.9999999999258762, \"rank\": 7.400291655665075e-11, \"text\": \"Peacock\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Peafowl\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Peafowl\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"NBC and Peacock will present live coverage of theOpening Ceremonyon Friday, July 26, beginning at Noon ET.\", \"from\": 2804, \"to\": 2910, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2804, \"end\": 2807, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC_Sports\", \"score\": 0.995919019876006, \"rank\": 0.004084460172050508, \"text\": \"NBC\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC_Sports\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC_Sports\"}, {\"begin\": 2812, \"end\": 2819, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Peafowl\", \"score\": 0.9999999999258762, \"rank\": 7.400291655665075e-11, \"text\": \"Peacock\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Peafowl\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Peafowl\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Telemundo will provide Spanish-language coverage beginning at 1 p.m.\", \"from\": 2911, \"to\": 2979, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2911, \"end\": 2920, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Telemundo\", \"score\": 0.9999998984762948, \"rank\": 8.373209075982148e-08, \"text\": \"Telemundo\", \"types\": [\"Q